##Gates leaves Microsoft's board in favor of a new coronavirus rapid detection tool

The Gates Foundation will provide up to $60 million to accelerate the identification, development and testing of vaccines, treatments and diagnostic tools for COVID-19

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
By Zhou Yuan, CAIJING correspondent

Editor | Sheryl Rong

On March 14, Microsoft announced that its CO founder and technical advisor, Bill, had been hired by Microsoft to run the company. Bill Gates steps down as Microsoft director to focus more on philanthropy.

Bill, 1975. Gates and Paul. Ellen co-founded Microsoft. Gates was CEO Until 2000, when he was replaced by Stevie Ballmer. Microsoft's current CEO Nadella took over in 2014.

Although Gates only stepped down as chairman of Microsoft's board in 2014, he has been involved in the Bill and Melinda Gates since 2008.

Gates is one of Microsoft's largest shareholders, with a 1.36 percent stake, according to the company's annual report. The company, which went public in 1986, now has a market capitalisation of more than a trillion dollars, making it one of the world's most valuable technology companies.

In the immediate aftermath of the COVID-19 outbreak in China, the Gates Foundation announced a $5 million emergency grant to fight the epidemic in China. At the time of the global epidemic, the Gates Foundation announced a commitment of up to $100 million in grants to support the global response to the epidemic.

TECH MOGUL TURNS PHILANTHROPIST FOR 10 years

In January 2000, Bill Gates and his wife, Melinda Gates, founded the Bill and Melinda Gates, based in Seattle, USA. The foundation is a non-profit organization dedicated to applying human ingenuity to reducing inequalities in health and development.

Since its creation, the Gates foundation has spread its philanthropy around the world. In 2000, $210 million was donated to help foreign students study at the University of Oxford; in January 2005, $750 million was donated to the Gavi Alliance; and in 2004, a total of $3 million was donated through various charities to victims of the Indian Ocean earthquake disaster, $50 million was donated in 2014 to help west African countries fight the Ebola epidemic, and so on.

In 2007, the Gates Foundation opened a representative office in Beijing to support China's efforts to improve public health and eradicate extreme poverty.

Since 2009, the Gates foundation has been working with the NCHK to develop and implement new models for TB and mdr-tb prevention and control to improve the quality of TB prevention and control in China, especially mdr-tb.

Tuberculosis (TB) is one of the major public health challenges in the world, and the 2030 agenda for sustainable development (2030 agenda) of the United Nations sets the goal of ending the TB epidemic by 2030. In recent years, the Chinese government has made great progress in the prevention and control of tuberculosis. The burden of tuberculosis has dropped significantly, and the United Nations Millennium Development Goals have been achieved five years ahead of schedule. But China is still one of the countries with high burden of TB, with about 900,000 new cases of TB every year, and high drug resistance rates in some regions.

From 2016 to 2019, the china-gai Tuberculosis Control Project comprehensively promoted the integrated control model in Zhejiang, Jilin and Ningxia provinces, covering a population of 90 million, the three provinces were able to meet the key targets of the National TB fifteen programme ahead of schedule, and both the disease control and social effects were visible: Ten years ago, it took two months to diagnose drug resistant TB, it now takes just two hours to use the new technology; a decade ago, people with TB needed 13 pills a day; now they need only three; under traditional Second Line Treatment, the cure rate for drug resistant TB is around 50% on average, now with the introduction of new drugs into the programme, preliminary results show that the cure rate for patients can be increased to 85 per cent, and thanks to the government's increased spending on tuberculosis and multi-sector funding, the cost of treating drug-resistant patients is now, personal contribution not exceeding 10% .

In November 2019, the Gates Foundation further reached an agreement with the NHRC to continue to work together to advance TB control in China over the next decade.

On January 27,2020, the Gates Foundation announced an emergency grant of $5 million, with technical and expert support, in the wake of the new crown pneumonia outbreak, to help Chinese partners speed up work on the epidemiology of COVID-19 infection, emergency intervention implementation, and pharmaceutical product development.

Started looking at pandemics five years ago

A prediction made five years ago by the Bill Gates went viral on Chinese social media after the new crown pneumonia outbreak.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Bill Gates's Ted talk, 2015

In 2015, the Bill Gates sounded the alarm about the threat of a global pandemic and called on the world to prepare for it in a war like fashion.

In 2018, the Bill Gates reiterated that view, citing research from the Disease Modeling Institute (IDM) , which said a pandemic could kill as many as 33 million people worldwide within six months.

"We lack a sense of urgency in the face of biological threats, " Gates said at the time. These preparations include simulations, military exercises and war-preparedness exercises so that we can better understand how disease will spread and how to respond to responses such as isolation and communications to minimize panic."

New Crown Pneumonia has spread in many parts of the world, the World Health Organization WHO as a global "pandemic" , the global countries to fight the epidemic has become very urgent.

On February 5th the Gates Foundation announced a pledge of up to $100m in grants to support the global response to the new pneumonia outbreak. The money will be used to strengthen case detection, isolation and treatment, protect vulnerable populations and accelerate the development of vaccines, drugs and Diagnostics, it said. The total newly announced grants includes $10 million that the foundation pledged in late January to fight the epidemic.

"multilateral institutions, governments, the private sector and charities must work together to contain the epidemic, help countries protect the most vulnerable and accelerate the development of tools, " said Gates Sussman, Chief Executive of the foundation, "We want to invest more resources to help generate a rapid and effective international response that is guided by science, not fear, and builds on the steps taken by the World Health Organization. "

The Gates Foundation is working closely with other donors to contribute more resources to assist the WHO, Chinese agencies and other international and national agencies.

The Gates Foundation has decided to provide up to $60 million to accelerate the identification, development and testing of vaccines, treatments and diagnostic tools for COVID-19, foreign media reported. If the virus continues to spread in the coming months or longer, only the search for safe and effective vaccines and treatments will lead to long-term effective control of the epidemic and a reduction in cases and deaths.
